From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shadow <shadow@code-puppy.dev>
Date: Fri, 04 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix: add iteration limit to llama_params_fit binary search

The binary search in llama_params_fit_impl (Step 4: MoE layer filling)
can loop infinitely when the memory measurements don't converge for
MoE models. Each iteration loads the full model from disk, so even
a finite but large iteration count causes multi-minute hangs.

Add a 32-iteration limit. If convergence isn't reached, use the
last known good configuration. This is more than sufficient for
the binary search to converge on well-behaved models.

---
 src/llama.cpp | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/llama.cpp b/src/llama.cpp
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/src/llama.cpp
+++ b/src/llama.cpp
@@ -626,7 +626,8 @@ static void llama_params_fit_impl(
         if (mem_high[id] > targets[id]) {
             assert(ngl_per_device_high[id].n_full() >= ngl_per_device[id].n_full());
             uint32_t delta = ngl_per_device_high[id].n_full() - ngl_per_device[id].n_full();
-            while (delta > 1) {
+            int fit_iter = 0;
+            while (delta > 1 && fit_iter++ < 32) {
                 uint32_t step_size = int64_t(delta) * (targets[id] - mem[id]) / (mem_high[id] - mem[id]);
                 step_size = std::max(step_size, uint32_t(1));
                 step_size = std::min(step_size, delta - 1);
--
